The DXM75N600X6178 is built in accordance with the standard DXM specifications with the following exceptions.

The unit will be used for supplying an RTW X-ray tube model MCDH 75B-1,5/1,5 80° x 10°.

1. Filament Calibration: Calibrate with a .75-meter-high voltage cable at 3.7A and 11V rms.
2. Filament Limit: An absolute maximum of 3.7A for filament current will be stored in the units firmware.
3. The maximum emission current shall be 10.0mA. The power supply can provide this current at 60kV max. Maximum output power is 600W.
4. Current scaling is 4095=10.0mA.
5. Power Limit:   If the high voltage output power exceeds 630W the following will occur:  The high voltage output will be disabled. 
This fault is indicated by illumination of over current led status LED on the front cover and as power limiting fault flag via command 68.

Request Faults
Description:
The host requests that the firmware report Faults.
Direction:  Host to supply
Syntax:  <STX><68><,><ETX>
Response:  <STX><68><,><ARG1><,><ARG2><,><ARG3><,><ARG4><,><ARG5><,><ARG6><,><ETX>
Where:
<ARGx> 1 = Fault, 0 = No Fault in ASCII format
ARG1 = ARC
ARG2 = Over Temperature
ARG3 = Over Voltage
ARG4 = Under Voltage
ARG5 = Over Current

Input Current:			4.3 Amps.

The DXM75N600X6178 is built in accordance with the standard DXM specifications with the following exceptions.

The unit will be used for supplying an RTW X-ray tube model MCDH 75B-1,5/1,5 80° x 10°.

1. Filament Calibration: Calibrate with a .75-meter-high voltage cable at 3.7A and 11V rms.
2. Filament Limit: An absolute maximum of 3.7A for filament current will be stored in the units firmware.
3. The maximum emission current shall be 10.0mA. The power supply can provide this current at 60kV max. Maximum output power is 600W.
4. Current scaling is 4095=10.0mA.
5. Power Limit:   If the high voltage output power exceeds 630W the following will occur:  The high voltage output will be disabled. 
This fault is indicated by illumination of over current led status LED on the front cover and as power limiting fault flag via command 68.

Request Faults
Description:
The host requests that the firmware report Faults.
Direction:  Host to supply
Syntax:  <STX><68><,><ETX>
Response:  <STX><68><,><ARG1><,><ARG2><,><ARG3><,><ARG4><,><ARG5><,><ARG6><,><ETX>
Where:
<ARGx> 1 = Fault, 0 = No Fault in ASCII format
ARG1 = ARC
ARG2 = Over Temperature
ARG3 = Over Voltage
ARG4 = Under Voltage
ARG5 = Over Current

Standard Specifications:
Output Voltage:			75kV negative.
Output Current:			10mA.
Input Voltage:			200-240Vac ±10%.
Input Current:			4.3 Amps.
Agency marks:			Compliant to ECC low voltage directive and EEC EMC directive. Unit is RoHS compliant. Shall have CE mark.

The DXM75N600X6178 is built in accordance with the standard DXM specifications with the following exceptions.

The unit will be used for supplying an RTW X-ray tube model MCDH 75B-1,5/1,5 80° x 10°.

1. Filament Calibration: Calibrate with a .75-meter-high voltage cable at 3.7A and 11V rms.
2. Filament Limit: An absolute maximum of 3.7A for filament current will be stored in the units firmware.
3. The maximum emission current shall be 10.0mA. The power supply can provide this current at 60kV max. Maximum output power is 600W.
4. Current scaling is 4095=10.0mA.
5. Power Limit:   If the high voltage output power exceeds 630W the following will occur:  The high voltage output will be disabled. 
This fault is indicated by illumination of over current led status LED on the front cover and as power limiting fault flag via command 68.

Request Faults
Description:
The host requests that the firmware report Faults.
Direction:  Host to supply
Syntax:  <STX><68><,><ETX>
Response:  <STX><68><,><ARG1><,><ARG2><,><ARG3><,><ARG4><,><ARG5><,><ARG6><,><ETX>
Where:
<ARGx> 1 = Fault, 0 = No Fault in ASCII format
ARG1 = ARC
ARG2 = Over Temperature
ARG3 = Over Voltage
ARG4 = Under Voltage
ARG5 = Over Current

Standard Specifications:
Output Voltage:			75kV negative.
Output Current:			10mA.
Input Voltage:			200-240Vac ±10%.
Input Current:			4.3 Amps.
Agency marks:			Compliant to ECC low voltage directive and EEC EMC directive. Unit is RoHS compliant. Shall have CE mark.

The DXM75N600X6178 is built in accordance with the standard DXM specifications with the following exceptions.

The unit will be used for supplying an RTW X-ray tube model MCDH 75B-1,5/1,5 80° x 10°.

1. Filament Calibration: Calibrate with a .75-meter-high voltage cable at 3.7A and 11V rms.
2. Filament Limit: An absolute maximum of 3.7A for filament current will be stored in the units firmware.
3. The maximum emission current shall be 10.0mA. The power supply can provide this current at 60kV max. Maximum output power is 600W.
4. Current scaling is 4095=10.0mA.
5. Power Limit:   If the high voltage output power exceeds 630W the following will occur:  The high voltage output will be disabled. 
This fault is indicated by illumination of over current led status LED on the front cover and as power limiting fault flag via command 68.

Request Faults
Description:
The host requests that the firmware report Faults.
Direction:  Host to supply
Syntax:  <STX><68><,><ETX>
Response:  <STX><68><,><ARG1><,><ARG2><,><ARG3><,><ARG4><,><ARG5><,><ARG6><,><ETX>
Where:
<ARGx> 1 = Fault, 0 = No Fault in ASCII format
ARG1 = ARC
ARG2 = Over Temperature
ARG3 = Over Voltage
ARG4 = Under Voltage
ARG5 = Over Current

Standard Specifications:
Output Voltage:			75kV negative.
Output Current:			10mA.
Input Voltage:			200-240Vac ±10%.
Input Current:			4.3 Amps.
Agency marks:			Compliant to ECC low voltage directive and EEC EMC directive. Unit is RoHS compliant. Shall have CE mark.
